Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.95,0:01:33.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,May I ask a question?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.92,0:01:35.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Queen to F3.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.54,0:01:36.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.67,0:01:37.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,King to G7.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.00,0:01:41.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a good idea to send me into battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.38,0:01:42.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rook to E4.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.59,0:01:47.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I die, the Deucalion's Aldnoah will shut down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.22,0:01:48.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.80,0:01:50.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rook to D8.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.93,0:01:53.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we'll worry about that\Nwhen we have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.56,0:01:57.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to be removed from the\Nfront lines, Ensign Kaizuka?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.56,0:01:58.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.69,0:02:00.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go into battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.48,0:02:02.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Queen to F6, check.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.82,0:02:05.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,King to F6, king takes queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.87,0:02:07.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're in agreement, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.78,0:02:10.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bishop to E5, check.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.99,0:02:12.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll put it on the monitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.41,0:02:17.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come up with\Nthat move yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.21,0:02:20.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or is it something that analytical\Nengine of yours cooked up?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.38,0:02:22.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's mine, about 70-30.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.13,0:02:23.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,About 70-30?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.63,0:02:28.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm assigning tasks to unused brain cells\Nto try to optimize its processing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.80,0:02:33.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it's both the device's suggestion\Nand my own idea at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.85,0:02:37.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This ship and her crew\Nboth owe you our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.52,0:02:41.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to fight, I think\Nwe should support that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.98,0:02:48.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't deserve any special treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.11,0:02:51.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear that Aldnoah activation\Ntests were conducted
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.62,0:02:55.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,using blood samples that had\Nbeen drawn from the princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.12,0:02:58.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,King to G5.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.12,0:03:01.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Result, failure. Blood alone was not \Nsufficient for Aldnoah activation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.54,0:03:04.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you could be considered\Na special case indeed, Ensign.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.17,0:03:09.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When you resuscitated the princess, \Nthe activation factor transferred to...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.97,0:03:11.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,no, infected you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.61,0:03:14.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then it was fully activated when you \Ncame into contact with royal blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.14,0:03:17.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Over the past ten months or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.06,0:03:22.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we've obtained plenty of intel on\NAldnoah and their Kataphrakts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.65,0:03:27.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But they still have the overwhelming\Nedge in military strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.03,0:03:30.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no guarantee that we'll\Nwin if we keep on fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.24,0:03:34.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if we do, Ensign Kaizuka...\NI'll put my money on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.83,0:03:38.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bishop to G7.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.46,0:03:43.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you resign?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.50,0:03:46.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Was that move yours?\NOr your left eye's?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.88,0:03:49.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave that to your imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.02,0:04:01.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose not even the Tharsis\Ncan see that far into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.58,0:04:18.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.37,0:04:19.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.17,0:04:31.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Milord Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.47,0:04:35.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I clustered my shots in the region\Nthat you calculated, Mr. Harklight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.22,0:04:39.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let us pray that they won't be influenced \Nby some unexpected wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.22,0:04:43.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I thought I smelled something.\NA dog has snuck aboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.10,0:04:46.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A rather grubby one, at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.44,0:04:49.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.61,0:04:55.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good day, Count Barouhcruz.\NCount Marylcian.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.24,0:04:57.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I rushed here so that I might\Njoin in the battle as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.74,0:04:59.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Terran dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.12,0:05:01.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mind your tongue!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.96,0:05:08.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Saazbaum!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.46,0:05:11.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine Troyard here is my vassal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.30,0:05:14.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he has given some offense,\NI offer my apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.18,0:05:17.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, if this treatment is unwarranted,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.22,0:05:18.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Marylcian,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.35,0:05:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it will not go well for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.64,0:05:24.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If this Terran were merely your pet,\Nit would be eccentric, but tolerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.85,0:05:26.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But to appoint him a knight?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.69,0:05:29.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that not taking\Nyour game too far?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.19,0:05:34.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Barouhcruz, it is not your place\Nto offer opinions regarding my vassals.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.70,0:05:38.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps, but him fighting alongside us\Nis another matter entirely!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.58,0:05:40.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One cannot take to\Nthe field of battle
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.74,0:05:42.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,with someone who might\Nturn traitor at any moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.79,0:05:45.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that is your concern, please\Nstrike me down right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.75,0:05:50.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are entirely correct.\NIf I go into battle with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.63,0:05:53.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it might very well be me\Nwho is attacked from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.59,0:05:55.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.63,0:05:56.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Men!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.80,0:05:57.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hear me, all of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.81,0:06:03.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By the grace of the emperor of Vers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.31,0:06:08.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I name Slaine Troyard my son\Nright here and now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.36,0:06:12.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All of you here are my witnesses!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.07,0:06:15.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord Count...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.53,0:06:16.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stand, Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.41,0:06:20.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From this day forth,\Nyou are my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.20,0:06:25.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will you raise a hand to him\Neven now, Count Marylcian?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.58,0:06:31.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you are prepared to go\Nto such lengths, so be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.34,0:06:36.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if his behavior is the least bit suspicious,\NI will put him down without mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.14,0:06:43.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me. I have put you\Nin an awkward position.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.93,0:06:46.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is fine. I had decided\Nto do this long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.77,0:06:52.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I, too, take to the field of battle.\NI must have a successor just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.82,0:06:55.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, think of me as your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.70,0:07:08.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations, Milord Slaine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.67,0:07:14.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The count's heir... This puts you one\Nstep closer to your dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.80,0:07:17.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough, Mr. Harklight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.01,0:07:20.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.14,0:07:23.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.68,0:07:24.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.39,0:07:29.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think\Nwill win, Eddelrittuo?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.98,0:07:35.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The glorious Vers Imperial Forces\Nwill emerge victorious, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.78,0:07:37.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Doesn't that trouble you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.49,0:07:41.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have friends aboard a United\NEarth Forces ship, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.49,0:07:44.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perish the thought!\NFriends on Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.41,0:07:46.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. Let's have a wager, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.83,0:07:48.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A wager?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.00,0:07:50.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the Vers Empire wins, I bet...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.37,0:07:51.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let me think...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.62,0:07:54.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My sister's life, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.59,0:07:58.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.05,0:08:06.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you dreaming\Nof right now, sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.81,0:08:14.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you seen Inko?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.86,0:08:18.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The electromagnetic catapult, I think?\NShe's probably with Rayet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.57,0:08:19.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.99,0:08:21.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.40,0:08:22.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.45,0:08:26.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sweats?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.62,0:08:28.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're too greedy, Yutaro-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.66,0:08:34.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tharsis. Details of its abilities, unknown.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.79,0:08:37.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}High rate of attack evasion reported.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.13,0:08:39.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Confirmed pilot...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.18,0:08:44.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...Slaine Troyard.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.01,0:08:50.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A good luck charm given to me by a dear\NTerran friend when we arrived on Earth.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.06,0:08:52.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Animals that fly through the air...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.77,0:08:55.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It is just as you said, Slaine!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.56,0:08:59.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is he equipped with a neuro-linked\Nanalytical engine too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.95,0:09:05.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. But I don't\Nhave enough data.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.62,0:09:08.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It dodged my attacks as though\N it could see the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.37,0:09:13.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true...\Nit could be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.79,0:09:14.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You monologuing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.09,0:09:18.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was talking to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.55,0:09:20.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's what monologuing means.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.13,0:09:28.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The warrior god Odin, rider of the\Nmythological, eight-legged Sleipnir,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.14,0:09:32.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,drank of the waters of Mímisbrunnr\Nand was granted vast wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.64,0:09:37.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But the price he paid for that\Nwisdom was his left eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.06,0:09:39.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Norse mythology.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.23,0:09:40.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Know-it-all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.36,0:09:42.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make fun of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.61,0:09:49.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After the battle in Russia,\NI wanted off the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.04,0:09:52.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was terrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.31,0:09:57.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But then it hit me that if I did, I'd never be\Nable to look Okojo in the eye when I do die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.63,0:10:02.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If your steed is ever acting up,\Ncome see me day or night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.80,0:10:04.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fix it up in a flash.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.80,0:10:05.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hold you to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.26,0:10:11.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, why don't we grab a bite before\Nthe battle? There's still some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.31,0:10:12.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.56,0:10:16.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I was shot, my stomach\Nwas empty, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.02,0:10:20.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They say I would've died if my organs had\Nbeen contaminated by stomach contents.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.32,0:10:21.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.15,0:10:26.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I might not get another\Nchance, so maybe some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.20,0:10:29.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are his reel selections?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.57,0:10:35.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's got a #1 through #3, a #10 for\Nemergencies, and one on the left and right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.41,0:10:37.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's specced out for high-G pivots.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.42,0:10:39.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Long, thin wires aren't cut out for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.50,0:10:40.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Found you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.46,0:10:42.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's Team Deucalion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.46,0:10:45.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you're the Aldnoah unit that\Neverybody's talking about, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.05,0:10:46.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hear one of you is a Martian.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.80,0:10:50.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get in our way on\Nthe battlefield, little ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.89,0:10:55.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What was their problem?\NBunch of jerks!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.35,0:10:56.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're not wrong, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.94,0:10:59.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All Martians are the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.19,0:11:03.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know that better than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.40,0:11:09.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're so adorable, Rayet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.95,0:11:11.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You've got the "tsun" part down pat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.28,0:11:12.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.08,0:11:14.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wish you'd show a little\Nmore "dere," though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.20,0:11:15.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.20,0:11:16.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Want some candy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.50,0:11:17.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna deck you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.46,0:11:20.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We will enter defense airspace in 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.21,0:11:22.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.46,0:11:23.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good hunting!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.34,0:11:29.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my steed ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.55,0:11:31.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The fine-tuning has been completed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.80,0:11:32.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.39,0:11:36.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dioscuria II, launching!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.69,0:11:45.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine Troyard, launching in the Tharsis.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.74,0:11:48.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stygis Squadron, launching!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.96,0:12:03.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Martian Kataphrakt squadron approaching!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.04,0:12:05.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Calling all forces!\NCommence operation!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.88,0:12:09.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Message from HQ!\NCommence operation!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.17,0:12:10.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Deucalion, launch!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.34,0:12:14.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We will provide support for the attack\Nplatoons as a guerrilla force.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.97,0:12:16.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All hands to battle stations.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.72,0:12:20.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our shipboard Kataphrakts are\Nlaunching from Trident Base.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.48,0:12:24.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mustang 11, cleared for launch!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.15,0:12:28.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Roger. Mustang 11, cleared for launch!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.90,0:12:29.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Blastoff!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.95,0:12:37.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Blastoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.80,0:12:55.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Target merge. Commencing attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.35,0:13:04.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Attack incoming!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.60,0:13:08.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hold your fire! They can't hit us\Nin this wind, anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.15,0:13:09.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hit them when they get in close!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.90,0:13:13.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hit them when they get in close...\NHit them when they get in close...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.32,0:13:16.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My umbrella's been hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.91,0:13:19.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mustang 11!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.12,0:13:23.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine, but the debris is not! I can't \Nget a clear shot with all this shaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.87,0:13:26.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mustang 00, moving to assist.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.67,0:13:33.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Inaho!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.26,0:13:38.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey, what about your umbrella?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.85,0:13:41.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a drizzle. I don't need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.10,0:13:42.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Stop pulling crazy stunts, darn it!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.85,0:13:44.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be able to use it\Nin a dogfight anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.40,0:13:48.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inferring gravitational shifts.\NData compensation, ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.52,0:13:50.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.07,0:13:52.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Commence attack!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.46,0:13:56.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.12,0:14:07.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pivoting via wire swing-by.\NReturning to combat airspace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.96,0:14:09.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,#3, shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.55,0:14:23.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pivot complete in 4, 3, 2, 1... Release.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.91,0:14:38.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho Kaizuka...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.53,0:14:40.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine Troyard...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.45,0:14:47.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Marineros Base will make\Nnext approach in 30 seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.58,0:14:49.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Main guns ready to fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.21,0:14:51.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Attention, all platoons!\NGet clear of our line of fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.00,0:14:54.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rayet!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.84,0:14:58.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is Rhinelander 22!\NCrap, I've got one on my six!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.51,0:15:02.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Roger. Mustang 22, moving to assist.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.52,0:15:09.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Martian!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.94,0:15:14.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Marineros Base now in firing range.\NNo friendly units in line of fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.61,0:15:15.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Main guns, fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.37,0:15:25.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Marineros Base beginning to move away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.00,0:15:29.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Issue disengage order to attack platoons\Nand guerrilla unit! Put them on defense!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.42,0:15:32.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho, we've been ordered\Nto disengage! Come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.38,0:15:34.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.55,0:15:42.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's some accurate shooting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.31,0:15:49.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it, he's using predictions, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.56,0:15:50.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,#1, pivot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.07,0:16:01.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait until the instant\Nhe comes out of the rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.20,0:16:05.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He'll attack the instant\NI come out from the rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.54,0:16:09.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Coordinates confirmed.\NTwo minutes to impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.67,0:16:11.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.71,0:16:13.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.51,0:16:24.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hit him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.26,0:16:27.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.02,0:16:30.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you all right, Slaine? Fall back.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.48,0:16:32.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, I can still fight!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.48,0:16:33.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't overdo it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.02,0:16:37.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The orange Kataphrakt...\NI owe him some payback!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.08,0:16:49.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for the gap in my barrier?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.15,0:16:51.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I took the liberty of \Nchanging its location.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.42,0:16:57.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fly, my servants!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.78,0:17:24.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Energy joints, linked.\NBlade field, engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.04,0:17:29.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sword drawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.92,0:17:40.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.67,0:17:42.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Inaho!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.47,0:17:44.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll cover you! Get away, Inaho!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.88,0:17:46.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stay back, Inko!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.05,0:17:46.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.80,0:17:47.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stay there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.51,0:17:49.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Right at that position!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.76,0:17:52.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare to meet your maker, Terran!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.39,0:17:55.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right kick thruster jettisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.73,0:17:56.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.90,0:18:05.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The flames aren't being sucked in!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.53,0:18:06.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The barrier gap!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.79,0:18:17.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You won't get away! Slaine!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.76,0:18:27.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's that?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.72,0:18:30.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A high-speed debris cluster.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.01,0:18:33.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I picked up a debris cloud closing in\Nat high speed on my 3D Doppler radar.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.44,0:18:38.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thanks, Inko. A split second later,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.81,0:18:41.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and I'd have been caught in it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.99,0:18:49.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible! My Dioscuria,\Nbrought low by mere debris?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.16,0:18:50.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That wasn't debris.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.28,0:18:52.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.95,0:18:55.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I fired them off before the battle began.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.83,0:18:59.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They were aimed so that they\Nwould swing around the Earth{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.17,0:19:01.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and land at that spot right now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.50,0:19:04.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Slaine?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.17,0:19:08.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I had originally meant it as a\Ntrap to defeat Inaho Kaizuka.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.34,0:19:10.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The trick was to disable\Nyour dimensional barrier,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.43,0:19:13.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but I thought that if anyone\Ncould manage it, it was him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.64,0:19:14.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.39,0:19:16.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shut up!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.98,0:19:23.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Did you honestly believe that\NI would swear fealty to you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.24,0:19:28.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To the man who pulled the trigger\Nagainst Princess Asseylum?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.20,0:19:31.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Did you think I would forgive you?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.04,0:19:38.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My second volley will arrive soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.33,0:19:39.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.92,0:19:44.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.18,0:19:51.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not too shabby.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.99,0:20:14.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On this day, I have lost\Nmy second father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.66,0:20:19.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was also a great man\Nwho devoted his life
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.71,0:20:21.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to the prosperity\Nof the Vers Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.38,0:20:26.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hereby announce my resolve\Nto carry on both my fathers' legacy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.50,0:20:31.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and fight for the even greater\Nprosperity of the Vers Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.76,0:20:33.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}Lords of the Vers Orbital Knights.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.22,0:20:36.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}This is no time to be squabbling\Namongst each other.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.06,0:20:40.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}As knights of the noble Vers Empire,\Nshould we not work{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.10,0:20:44.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}hand in hand to eradicate\NEarth's resistance forces?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.90,0:20:48.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}In the name of Her Imperial Highness\NAsseylum Vers Allusia!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.40,0:20:52.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}Let us punish the Terrans who\Ndare defy the Vers Empire!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.19,0:20:51.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't lying...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.53,0:20:56.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}Her Highness Asseylum is biding\Nher time at our lunar base!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.62,0:20:58.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it... She's alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.66,0:20:58.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}In hopes that she may remain—{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.92,0:21:07.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord, you must be exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.55,0:21:14.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Harklight, you were born into\Nthe third class, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.22,0:21:15.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.26,0:21:18.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Though they were poor\Nand of a low class,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.18,0:21:20.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,my father and mother\Nworked hard to raise me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.89,0:21:25.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and used every means at their disposal\Nso that I could serve the Orbital Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.90,0:21:32.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord Slaine, it is for that reason that\NI have the utmost respect for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.49,0:21:36.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You, who have attained the rank of\Ncount even though you are a Terran.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.42,0:21:48.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This new era will be\Nfor people like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.71,0:21:51.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's begin, Harklight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.38,0:21:54.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.97,0:21:59.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Count Slaine Saazbaum Troyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.89,0:22:09.89,T1,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pivoting Trap
